member.remarks:
Returns null if the value was not set at the data source or
if the value at the data source cannot be converted to a bool value using System.Convert.ToBoolean(object)
method.

member.summary:
Returns the value of this property as a string. Returns "null" if the value was not set at the data source
if the value at the data source cannot be converted to a bool value using System.Convert.ToString(object)
method.

member.param:
true if this tree provider will automatically publish updates
when the underlying data changes;
false if it should not or cannot due to the underlying data store not supporting push notifications.

A value indicating whether the returned task
            should be completed when all the currently queued tasks are completed;
            use false to fully drain the queue (including of tasks that are registered after this call).

